label: Study identifiers for internal use by ClinEpiDB staff
Additional data
definition: VEuPathDB.org site(s) where additional study data can be accessed.

label: Data access level
definition: There are five categories of data access restrictions, which differ in what levels of access are required to see aggregated vs disaggregated data. Aggregated data includes what can be seen in the �Browse and subset� and �Visualize� tabs, while disaggregated data includes what can be seen in filed downloaded from the �Download� tab. (i) Public: No access restrictions. Users can view and download the data as �Guests� without logging in. (ii) Controlled: Guest users can view aggregated data via the �Browse and subset� and �Visualize� tabs, but must register and request access to download data. The request may be submitted via a form that pops up when a user logs in with a registered account and clicks on any file in the �Download� tab. Data can be downloaded by the registered user immediately following request submission. (iii) Protected: Guest users can view aggregated data via the �Browse and subset� and �Visualize� tabs, but must register, request, and obtain approval from the data providers to download data. The request may be submitted via a form that pops up when a registered user is logged in and clicks on any file in the �Download� tab. (iv) Private: A registered user must request and obtain approval to access any aspect of the data. The request may be submitted via a form that pops up when a registered user is logged in and clicks on the study. (v) Prerelease: The study is under active development for future release, and only the study team can access the data. Guest and registered users can view the study page only.

label: Percent approved
definition: The percent of data access requests received from ClinEpiDB website users that were approved by the original study team.

label: Total requests
definition: Number of data access requests received from ClinEpiDB website users. The number of requests for "Public" studies are not recorded.

label: Disease
definition: Classification of disease(s) investigated by the study.

label: WHO indicator subdomain
definition: Categorization of core health indicators about the quality, risk, or access to health care deemed clinically significant by the World Health Organization.

label: Build date for current release
definition: Date the dataset was released onto the ClinEpiDB website in its current form.

label: Build number for current release
definition: Website build number for the release of the dataset in its current form onto ClinEpiDB.org.

label: Build number introduced
definition: Website build number for the first time the dataset was released onto ClinEpiDB.org.

label: Variable count
definition: The number of variables in the dataset.

label: Household count
definition: The number of households surveyed in the dataset.

label: Participant count
definition: The number of participants surveyed in the dataset.

label: Participant repeated measures count
definition: The number of unique observations of participants in the dataset.

label: Samples count
definition: The number of samples investigated in the dataset.

label: Sample type
definition: Type(s) of sample collected in the study.

label: Data collection start year
definition: Year in which data collection started.

label: Data collection stop year
definition: Year in which data collection ended.

label: Project name
definition: Whether the study was part of a larger project, or collection of related studies.

label: Contact Name
definition: Name of the person to contact on the original study team.

label: Contact Institution
definition: Contact institution for the original study team.
